==========================================
Representation of negative integer in Binary (2C)

How to represent negative in computer. It is just zero and one.
Sign-magitude.

For example 
0001 is a positive 1
but
1001 is negative 1. The leading # indicates the sign of the number.

1 complement. (1C)
Simply flip each digit to represent negative.

2's Complement (2C)

for example the decimal 5 is 0101

To make it negative just flip the binary i.e 1010 (like in 1C)
But as per 2c just add 1 to the least significant number in binary. i.e 1011

Also remember to throw away the carry out . Meaning overflow is going to get a new defination. 

=================================
Arithmetic in 2C:


Sign Extension: When we need to add number with different lengths. Unsigned numbers is easy just padd is but signed means number with negative. 

positive just add zeros padd it with
it negative padd it with 1 ok.

This is how the sign extension works. 

